            <fr:title text="Centralizes">Centralizes</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Bourbaki's <fr:link href="/bourbaki-1974-algebra/" title="Algebra, Chapters 1-3" uri="http://localhost:8000/bourbaki-1974-algebra/" display-uri="bourbaki-1974-algebra" type="local">Algebra, Chapters 1-3</fr:link> I ยง5.3</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gr-000G/" title="Group" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-000G/" display-uri="gr-000G" type="local">Group</fr:link>.</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  G]]></fr:tex> be an element, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subset. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Centralizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ab=ba]]></fr:tex>. In other words, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  C_{G}(B)]]></fr:tex> is an element of the <fr:link href="/gr-001O/" title="Centralizer of a subset" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-001O/" display-uri="gr-001O" type="local">centralizer</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
<html:li>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be subsets. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Centralizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if every element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> centralizes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>; i.e., <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq  C_{G}(B)]]></fr:tex> is a subset of the centralizer of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
<html:li>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq  G]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gr-001B/" title="Subgroup" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-001B/" display-uri="gr-001B" type="local">Subgroup</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subset. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Centralizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h\in  H]]></fr:tex> centralizes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>. In other words, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq  C_{G}(B)]]></fr:tex> is a subgroup of the centralizer of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
            <html:p>In the preceding three definitions, we may replace <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> with a subgroup <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K\leq  G]]></fr:tex> or an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  G]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
