            <fr:title text="Normalizes">Normalizes</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Bourbaki's <fr:link href="/bourbaki-1974-algebra/" title="Algebra, Chapters 1-3" uri="http://localhost:8000/bourbaki-1974-algebra/" display-uri="bourbaki-1974-algebra" type="local">Algebra, Chapters 1-3</fr:link> I ยง5.3</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gr-000G/" title="Group" uri="http://localhost:8000/gr-000G/" display-uri="gr-000G" type="local">Group</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  G]]></fr:tex> be an element. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Normalizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a^{-1}Ba=B]]></fr:tex>; in other words <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  N_{G}(B)]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
<html:li>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Normalizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if every element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> normalizes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
<html:li>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq  G]]></fr:tex> be a subgroup of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn>Normalizes</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> if every element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> normalizes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
            <html:p>We can replace <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> with a subgroup <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K\leq  G]]></fr:tex> and the definition of "normalizes" generalizes accordingly; and we can replace <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> with an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>, and the definition "normalizes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>" is just a synonym for "normalizes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{b\}]]></fr:tex>".</html:p>
